To understand Lithic=E2=80=99s opportunity, we need to start in the nitty g=
ritty: by understanding how payments work.=C2=A0
The Anatomy of a Payment
Moving money around is complex.=C2=A0
We make payments all day, every day. It=E2=80=99s early on the east coast, =
so I haven=E2=80=99t made one yet this morning, but judging by my credit ca=
rd statement, I=E2=80=99ll make between three to five payments by the time =
I go to sleep tonight. Most of us never think about what goes on behind the=
 scenes; we just swipe our card or enter our card details online and trust =
that the balance will go down in our account and the balance will go up in =
the account of whoever we=E2=80=99re buying from.=C2=A0
In between those two events, though, a bunch of stuff happens. In fact, the=
re are at least five layers between the buyer and the merchant. I say =E2=
=80=9Cat least,=E2=80=9D because many of these layers have multiple parties=
 involved. Finix did a great job of breaking it down in Understanding the P=
ayments Stack [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkM1uhSAQRp_msrsGEBAXLLr=
paxiE0UuqYGCs9e3L1TRNCJN883OS4yzCnPJptlSQvL8Bzw1MhKMsgAiZ7AXyELxhiutWip54Iz=
