p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 =
1em 0;">Moving money around is complex.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a=
; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">We make payments =
all day, every day. It&#8217;s early on the east coast, so I haven&#8217;t =
made one yet this morning, but judging by my credit card statement, I&#8217=
;ll make between three to five payments by the time I go to sleep tonight. =
Most of us never think about what goes on behind the scenes; we just swipe =
our card or enter our card details online and trust that <strong>the balanc=
e will go down</strong> in our account and <strong>the balance will go up</=
strong> in the account of whoever we&#8217;re buying from.&nbsp;</p><p styl=
e=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;=
">In between those two events, though, a bunch of stuff happens. In fact, t=
here are at least five layers between the buyer and the merchant. I say &#8=
220;at least,&#8221; because many of these layers have multiple parties inv=
